        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 5:27PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 527 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles southeast of Red
Cloud Campground to 6 miles northeast of Box Butte Reservoir.
Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Box Butte Campground, Box Butte Reservoir, and Box Butte Dam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for
the Panhandle of Nebraska.</instruction>
